<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>About - ZapNotes</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-QWTKZyjpPEjISv5WaRU9OFeRpok6YctnYmDr5pNlyT2bRjXh0JMhjY6hW+ALEwIH" crossorigin="anonymous">
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js" integrity="sha384-YvpcrYf0tY3lHB60NNkmXc5s9fDVZLESaAA55NDzOxhy9GkcIdslK1eN7N6jIeHz" crossorigin="anonymous" defer></script>
    <link href="/css/headers.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="/css/sticky-footer.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="icon" href="/images/favicon.ico" type="image/x-icon">
    <style>
        html, body {
            height: 100%;
            margin: 0;
        }

        body {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        header, footer {
            flex-shrink: 0; /* Prevents shrinking of header/footer */
        }

        main {
            flex-grow: 1; /* Allows main to grow and fill the available space */
        }
    </style>  
</head>    
<body>
    <header>
        <!-- Use partials for modularity. In order to send variables to partials, pass them as objects in the include statement -->
        <!-- I wanted to use the Bootstrap 'active' class to highlight buttons depending on which button you click -->
        <%- include('partials/header', {activePage: 'about'}) %>
    </header>
    <main>
        <div class="px-3">
            <p class="display-6">ZapNotes is a web application demonstration built using the MERN stack (minus the R).</p>

            <p>The back-end is comprised of:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>MongoDB, which is used as the database.</li> 
                <li>The server runtime environment is provided by Node.js.</li>
                <li>Mongoose serves as the Object Data Modeling (ODM) library for MongoDB.</li>
                <li>Express acts as the web framework to handle server-side logic and routing.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Front-end:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>EJS, which is used as the templating engine to render dynamic HTML views.</li>
                <li>Bootstrap, which is applied as the front-end framework for styling and responsive design.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>ZapNotes showcases a full-stack application where the back-end manages data and logic, while the front-end provides an interactive user interface.</p>
        </div>
    </main>
    <footer>
        <%- include('partials/footer') %>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>